---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import Prose from '../components/Prose.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy" description="FormVault's privacy policy: what stays on your device, what we may collect, and what we never collect.">
	<Hero eyebrow="Legal" title="Privacy Policy" lead="Last updated: placeholder date." />

	<Prose>
		<div class="mb-6 rounded-md border border-border bg-surface px-4 py-3 text-xs text-subtle">
			Draft placeholder. This text has not been reviewed by a lawyer and should not be relied on as legal advice. Review before launch.
		</div>
		<p>
			FormVault (&ldquo;we&rdquo;, &ldquo;us&rdquo;) is a desktop application that stores personal reference information locally on your
			device. This policy describes what limited data we do collect, and - more importantly - what we do not.
		</p>
		<h2>What stays on your device</h2>
		<p>
			The vault itself - every field, value, category, attachment, and profile - is stored in a file on your local file system. FormVault
			does not upload, sync, or transmit vault contents to any server operated by us or a third party.
		</p>
		<h2>What we may collect</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Anonymous, aggregated crash reports (opt-in).</li>
			<li>Basic install and version information for update checks.</li>
			<li>Website analytics on this marketing site (not the desktop app).</li>
		</ul>
		<h2>What we do not collect</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>The contents of your vault.</li>
			<li>Field names, values, or attachments.</li>
			<li>Keystrokes, clipboard contents, or the identity of apps you paste into.</li>
		</ul>
		<h2>Backups and exports</h2>
		<p>You can export your vault to a local JSON file at any time. Backups you create are your responsibility to store securely.</p>
		<h2>Contact</h2>
		<p>Questions about this policy: privacy@formvault.example (placeholder).</p>
	</Prose>
</Layout>
